OL,3,CNewcastle underground: Inside the
OL,4,Ctunnel running below the city
OL,6,FA feat of Victorian engineering, the
OL,7,Funderground wagonway avoided levies
OL,8,Fcharged on the transportation of coal
OL,9,Fabove the ground.
OL,11,FKev Byrne, from the Ouseburn Trust,
OL,12,Fwhich now runs tours of the tunnel,
OL,13,Fsaid: "It was built when the
OL,14,Findustrial revolution was really in
OL,15,Ffull stream so in about 1835 there
OL,16,Fwere two gentlemen who wanted to be
OL,17,Fpart of the trend at the time. They
OL,18,Fstarted to extract coal out of the
OL,19,Fground up in Spital Tongues."
