OL,3,CNewcastle underground: Inside the
OL,4,Ctunnel running below the city
OL,6,FMr Byrne added: "It was used by the
OL,7,Fpeople, mostly from Byker, to come and
OL,8,Fhide out when the air raid siren
OL,9,Fsounded. You would have them down here
OL,10,Ffor maybe 12 hours at a time.
OL,12,F"They were down there for considerably
OL,13,Flonger than other towns and cities
OL,14,Fbecause the Luftwaffe was using
OL,15,FNewcastle as a navigational aid, so
OL,16,Fthey would fly over, drop their bombs
OL,17,Fand turn around and fly back."
OL,19,FAccess to the tunnel was once again
OL,20,Fblocked at the end of the war and it
OL,21,Fdid not reopen until this century.
